{quote}"index.queue.thread.count" sets the number of threads to be used for the reindex job. The value has to be in the range of 1 to 10 (inclusive), i.e. at least one thread but no more than 10 threads will be used.{quote}

Is there any specific reason to limit the indexing thread to be within 1 to 10? We should allow the users to set the limit of the indexing thread with a bigger range, or eventually a flexible number.

