I'd like to have some pages which open action items for specific labels.  Then I'd like a page which shows ALL other open items - without any label, but EXCLUDING those labels which have their dedicated pages.

The simplest would be if there was an exclude option on the filters (in this case, labels), so I can say on the label field something like !lable1, !lable2, and I get all tasks on pages EXCEPT those with either lable1 or lable2.

This concept could be applied to all filters (although I haven't thought through on which it makes sense).
